subsection_content:
Common symptoms of insomnia often include: (3)
Difficulty sleeping at night; Waking up easily at night or waking up too early; Fatigue, drowsiness, not feeling relaxed after sleep; Worry about sleep-related problems; Often tired and sleepy during the day; Irritability, anxiety, mood swings; Difficulty concentrating, forgetting quickly
